quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,51,"Most surely We will support Our messengers and those who believe, in this life, and on the Day the witnesses arise"
  40,52,"The Day when their excuses will not profit the wrongdoers, and the curse will be upon them, and they will have the Home of Misery"
  40,53,"We gave Moses guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the Scripture"
  40,54,A guide and a reminder for those endowed with reason
  40,55,"So be patient. The promise of God is true. And ask forgiveness for your sin, and proclaim the praise of your Lord evening and morning"
  40,56,"Those who dispute regarding God's revelations without any authority having come to them—there is nothing in their hearts but the feeling of greatness, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in God; for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Seeing"
  40,57,"Certainly the creation of the heavens and the earth is greater than the creation of humanity, but most people do not know"
  40,58,Not equal are the blind and the seeing. Nor are those who believe and work righteousness equal to the sinners. How little you reflect
  40,59,"Indeed, the Hour is coming; there is no doubt about it; but most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has said, 'Pray to Me, and I will respond to you. But those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell forcibly"